fields.description:
*Assessment*

While verifying EUCA-9846, it was noticed that when a stack fails to deploy because the timeout option passed during the CreateStack call was exceeded, in the stack events, the resources that failed to be created did not report back as CREATE_FAILED.  The resource in this situation should have the reason for the failure be "Resource creation cancelled".  This doesn't follow AWS behavior.

_Eucalyptus (resource AWS::EC2::Instance isn't reported as FAILED in stack events)_
{code}
# euform-describe-stack-events DockerStack --region admin-hspencer@group1 | grep CREATE_FAIL
EVENT	DockerStack	9c0cc68f-66c0-4354-a4e8-ae2f05ee4ac8	AWS::CloudFormation::Stack	DockerStack	arn:aws:cloudformation::439629811643:stack/DockerStack/1a772fc6-5d8b-40da-8fb6-35a8fd706ac9	2015-01-21T17:15:59.923Z	CREATE_FAILED	Stack creation timed out.

# euform-describe-stack-events DockerStack --region admin-hspencer@group1 | grep CREATE_COMPLETE
EVENT	DockerStack	MyEBSVolume1-CREATE_COMPLETE-1421860500076	AWS::EC2::Volume	MyEBSVolume1	vol-0baa0a45	2015-01-21T17:15:00.076Z	CREATE_COMPLETE
EVENT	DockerStack	DockerSecurityGroup-CREATE_COMPLETE-1421860482658	AWS::EC2::SecurityGroup	DockerSecurityGroup	DockerStack-DockerSecurityGroup-MNAHA93TXSW1I	2015-01-21T17:14:42.658Z	CREATE_COMPLETE

# euform-describe-stack-resources -n DockerStack --region admin-hspencer@group1
RESOURCE	DockerSecurityGroup	DockerStack-DockerSecurityGroup-MNAHA93TXSW1I	AWS::EC2::SecurityGroup		DELETE_COMPLETE
RESOURCE	DockerInstance	i-e517e737	AWS::EC2::Instance		DELETE_COMPLETE
RESOURCE	MyEBSVolume1	vol-0baa0a45	AWS::EC2::Volume		DELETE_COMPLETE
{code}

_AWS (each resource is reported in either CREATE_FAILED or CREATE_COMPLETED)_
{code}
$ aws cloudformation describe-stack-events --stack-name DockerStack --profile harold-work | grep CREATE_FAILED | awk '{print $3}'
